.TH "libnvme_transport_handle_set_timeout" 9 "libnvme_transport_handle_set_timeout" "June 2026" "libnvme API manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
libnvme_transport_handle_set_timeout \- Set the default command timeout
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" libnvme_transport_handle_set_timeout
.BI "(struct libnvme_transport_handle *hdl "  ","
.BI "__u32 timeout_ms "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "hdl" 12
Transport handle to configure
.IP "timeout_ms" 12
Timeout in milliseconds. A value of 0 means use the kernel
default (NVME_DEFAULT_IOCTL_TIMEOUT).
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Sets a default timeout that is applied to every passthrough command
submitted through \fIhdl\fP when the command's own timeout_ms field is 0.
Commands that set a non-zero timeout_ms override this default.
